Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre

Class Trigger

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.Trigger
All Implemented Interfaces:
Event, Logical, Simplifiable, Signed, Serializable, Comparable<Logical>
Direct Known Subclasses:
CompiledTrigger
public class Trigger extends Object implements Event
A trigger is an event that must occur when its precondition is satisfied. Triggers are commonly used for inference and updating beliefs, such as a when a character should observe a property that would would not otherwise observe as a result of an action. Because triggers are events, each defines a signature, precondition, an effect.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware
